Sheriff John Stone reported a potential death toll of 25, but later clarified that it was unconfirmed due to overlapping search areas.
By Wednesday, the count stood at 15, including the gunmen.
Concerns arose about student safety, with armed guards and strict permissions in place.
The tragedy at Columbine High School sparked reflections on societal issues and calls for unity.
Investigators continued their work, while the community mourned and sought healing.
The return to classes was delayed as funerals were ongoing.
Despite the darkness, there were signs of hope and solidarity emerging from the tragedy.
